Gyms that I have lifted at have always had a brotherhood atmosphere. Like locals go together to the shooting range, get beer, if someone needs help with a job like moving furniture or towing a vehicle he'll ask and a few gymgoers will volunteer to help him after the workout, etc.

I've gone on roadtrips and mountain climbs with people from my gym. I'm pretty sure if someone got in trouble everyone in the gym would be willing to get into a fight or shoot somebody to help him. Gyms should be almost like masonic lodges. A bunch of men ready to help each other

A bit of a random observation, but people who print out PDFs of books they read at like a Xerox/printing shop (or an office printer at their job, library printer, etc.) tend to usually be very easygoing and chill people. Like a guy who downloads books and then prints them is cool

People who buy the actual "official" edition from Amazog etc. are often a bit too dilettantish and tend to steer towards aestheticism, people who read libgen PDFs and ebooks from zlib etc. can be a bit too intense and intellectual in the dumb way. But the above is a happy medium.
